ARGUMENT

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | #P_sp | |- ( A. x x = y -> x = y ) |
| 2 | 1 | #P_con3i | |- ( -. x = y -> -. A. x x = y ) |
| 3 | 2 | #P_adantr | |- ( ( -. x = y /\ y = z ) -> -. A. x x = y ) |
| 4 |  | #P_equtrr | |- ( z = y -> ( x = z -> x = y ) ) |
| 5 | 4 | #P_equcoms | |- ( y = z -> ( x = z -> x = y ) ) |
| 6 | 5 | #P_con3rr3 | |- ( -. x = y -> ( y = z -> -. x = z ) ) |
| 7 | 6 | #P_imp | |- ( ( -. x = y /\ y = z ) -> -. x = z ) |
| 8 |  | #P_sp | |- ( A. x x = z -> x = z ) |
| 9 | 7, 8 | #P_nsyl | |- ( ( -. x = y /\ y = z ) -> -. A. x x = z ) |
| 10 |  | #P_axc9 | |- ( -. A. x x = y -> ( -. A. x x = z -> ( y = z -> A. x y = z ) ) ) |
| 11 | 3, 9, 10 | #P_sylc | |- ( ( -. x = y /\ y = z ) -> ( y = z -> A. x y = z ) ) |
| 12 | 11 | #P_ex | |- ( -. x = y -> ( y = z -> ( y = z -> A. x y = z ) ) ) |
| 13 | 12 | #P_pm2.43d | |- ( -. x = y -> ( y = z -> A. x y = z ) ) |
\
 Derive ~ ax-13 from ~ ax-c9 and other older axioms. This proof uses newer axioms ~ ax-4 and ~ ax-6 , but since these are proved from the older axioms above, this is acceptable and lets us avoid having to reprove several earlier theorems to use ~ ax-c4 and ~ ax-c10 . (Contributed by NM, 21-Dec-2015.)  (Proof modification is discouraged.) (New usage is discouraged.)
